Pt was in USOH out w/ wife to lunch Friday ( 3 d PTA ) before admission , ate onion soup and club sandwich , then on Sat felt nauseated , SOB , confused. Wife noted that pt could not lie down to sleep Sat night ( usually 3 pillow orthopnea ). Sx cont through Sun , wife brought to ED on Mon , day of admission. Pt recently in LRMC ED , rx for UTI 1/7 . In ED pt afebrile , HR 59 , BP 152/61 , Sa 97% on 4L NC. On exam found to have JVP elevated 12-14 cm H2O , bibasilar rales , dec breath sounds at bases , RRR , no murmurs , no gallops , 1+ pitting edema bilat LE. Labs significant for Na 144 Cl 113 , Hco3 19 , BUN 30 , Cr 1.9 , platelets 97. UA showed 15-20 WBC , 2-5 RBC. EKG was unchanged , CXR showed worsening bilat pleural effusions. Hospital Course: 1. CV- Pt was not r/o secondary to low probability of ischemia. CHF exacerbation likely secondary to Na overload from pt's meal the Friday before admission. Pt was diuresed gently with 20 lasix IV x 2 on the first day of admission and then received 20 po lasix on the day of discharge. The pt's pulmonary status and mental status improved with diuresis and his JVD decreased to approx 8 cm H2O on exam. 2. ID: pt w/ presumed UTI , rx w/ bactrim 3. Disposition: Pt was eval by PT , who made recs for home PT for the pt. This arrangement was satisfactory for the pt and his wife. He will follow up with all of his physicians with his regular scheduled appointments.
